**Chat Application**

This is a simple real-time chat application built with Node.js, Express, and WebSockets.

**Features**

- Real-time chat using WebSockets
- User-friendly UI
- Simple and clean design

**Prerequisites**

Make sure you have the following installed:

- node
- npm
- express
- moment

**Setup Instructions**

Follow these steps to clone and run the app locally:

1. Clone the repository

2. Install dependencies
```bash
    npm install

3. Start server
    node server.js

4. Open the app in your browser
    Go to: http://localhost:3000

**How to use the application**
The first page displays form to add the username, select the room and then join the room.
You can also create your room using Create room button.

You cannot add same username, username has to be unique.

After joinig the room it opens another page where on the left you can see the users in the particular room
and the room name.
On right is the chat panel where you can send messages to other users and also few chat formatting options are available.

The message sent by you will appear right and other user's messages will appear on left with the time and username details.

Also you will get the notifications in the chat panel when user leaves or joins the particular room.

To check the functionality, enter this url - http://localhost:3000 in multiple tabs of the browser.
Enter different username in each tab to act as differnt users and join the rooms. 

Things to check - try entering same username, select same rooms for multiple user functionality, check message alignment when sent by you and others, 
create rooms, use the that room name and join using other username to check for active users in the particular room, 
join and leave the room to check for notifications in chat panel and also check the active users when users leave and join the rooms.

Also check for the responsiveness of the application.
